This issue has been partially addressed — client-side Blazor WASM rendering is available via the `SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor` package (shipped in 2.88+ via PR #1811). The remaining request is server-side Blazor support.

For server-side Blazor scenarios today, you can render on the server using standard SkiaSharp and send encoded images to the client:

```csharp
// Server-side rendering workaround
using var surface = SKSurface.Create(new SKImageInfo(width, height));
var canvas = surface.Canvas;
// ... draw operations ...
using var image = surface.Snapshot();
using var data = image.Encode(SKEncodedImageFormat.Png, 100);
var base64 = Convert.ToBase64String(data.ToArray());
// Send base64 string to client as <img src="data:image/png;base64,..." />
```

True server-side Blazor Extension support (drawing commands marshaled over SignalR) would require significant architectural work. Keeping this open to track the remaining server-side feature.
